{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.31",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 31 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:1",
      "text": "I made a covenant with mine eyes, and I will not think upon a virgin.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:2",
      "text": "Now what portion has God given from above? and is there an inheritance given of the Mighty One from the highest?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:3",
      "text": "Alas! destruction to the unrighteous, and rejection to them that do iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:4",
      "text": "Will he not see my way, and number all my steps?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:5",
      "text": "But if I had gone with scorners, and if too my foot has hasted to deceit:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:6",
      "text": "(for I am weighed in a just balance, and the Lord knows my innocence:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:7",
      "text": "if my foot has turned aside out of the way, or if mine heart has followed mine eye, and if too I have touched gifts with my hands;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:8",
      "text": "then let me sow, and let others eat; and let me be uprooted on the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:9",
      "text": "If my heart has gone forth after another man's wife, and if I laid wait at her doors;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:10",
      "text": "then let my wife also please another, and let my children be brought low.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:11",
      "text": "For the rage of anger is not to be controlled, in the case of defiling another man's wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:12",
      "text": "For it is a fire burning on every side, and whomsoever it attacks, it utterly destroys.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:13",
      "text": "And if too I despised the judgment of my servant or my handmaid, when they pleaded with me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:14",
      "text": "what then shall I do if the Lord should try me? and if also he should at all visit me, can I make an answer?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:15",
      "text": "Were not they too formed as I also was formed in the womb? yea, we were formed in the same womb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:16",
      "text": "But the helpless missed not whatever need they had, and I did not cause the eye of the widow to fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:17",
      "text": "And if too I ate my morsel alone, and did not impart of it to the orphan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:18",
      "text": "(for I nourished them as a father from my youth, and guided them from my mother's womb.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:19",
      "text": "And if too I overlooked the naked as he was perishing, and did not clothe him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:20",
      "text": "and if the poor did not bless me, and their shoulders were not warmed with the fleece of my lambs;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:21",
      "text": "if I lifted my hand against an orphan, trusting that my strength was far superior to his:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:22",
      "text": "let then my shoulder start from the blade-bone, and my arm be crushed off from the elbow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:23",
      "text": "For the fear of the Lord constrained me, and I cannot bear up by reason of his burden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:24",
      "text": "If I made gold my treasure, and if too I trusted the precious stone;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:25",
      "text": "and if too I rejoiced when my wealth was abundant, and if too I laid my hand on innumerable treasures:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:26",
      "text": "(do we not see the shining sun eclipsed, and the moon waning? for they have not power to continue:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:27",
      "text": "and if my heart was secretly deceived, and if I have laid my hand upon my mouth and kissed it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:28",
      "text": "let this also then be reckoned to me as the greatest iniquity: for I should have lied against the Lord Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:29",
      "text": "And if too I was glad at the fall of mine enemies, and mine heart said, Aha!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:30",
      "text": "let then mine ear hear my curse, and let me be a by-word among my people in my affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:31",
      "text": "And if too my handmaids have often said, Oh that we might be satisfied with his flesh; (whereas I was very kind:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:32",
      "text": "for the stranger did not lodge without, and my door was opened to every one that came:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:33",
      "text": "or if too having sinned unintentionally, I hid my sin;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:34",
      "text": "(for I did not stand in awe of a great multitude, so as not to declare boldly before them:) and if too I permitted a poor man to go out of my door with an empty bosom:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:35",
      "text": "(Oh that I had a hearer,) and if I had not feared the hand of the Lord; and as to the written charge which I had against any one,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:36",
      "text": "I would place it as a chaplet on my shoulders, and read it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:37",
      "text": "And if I did not read it and return it, having taken nothing from the debtor:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:38",
      "text": "If at any time the land groaned against me, and if its furrows mourned together;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:39",
      "text": "and if I ate its strength alone without price, and if too I grieved the heart of the owner of the soil, by taking aught from him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.31.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:40",
      "text": "then let the nettle come up to me instead of wheat, and a bramble instead of barley. And Job ceased speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
